__d(function(g,r,i,a,m,e,d){"use strict";Object.defineProperty(e,'__esModule',{value:!0}),Object.defineProperty(e,"TUTORIAL_STEPS",{enumerable:!0,get:function(){return t}});const t=[{tab:null,title:'Welcome',text:'So. You wish to train your ear. Good \u2014 I am Ludwig van Beethoven, and I shall show you around. I lost my hearing and still heard symphonies; imagine what you might do with two working ears and two minutes of attention.'},{tab:null,title:'Getting around',text:'This \u2261 button hides the settings \u2014 reference pitch, sound libraries, chord-label style, and this very tour, should you wish to endure me twice. The row of icons beside it moves you between the five rooms of this studio.',targetId:'menu'},{tab:'studio',title:'The Studio \xb7 adding instruments',text:'Here you assemble a chord one instrument at a time. Press "+ Add Instrument", choose an orchestral voice, pick its note, and play it \u2014 it sustains until you say otherwise. Each instrument gets its own card to adjust or silence.',targetId:'studio-add'},{tab:'studio',title:'Naming the chord',text:'Stack several notes and this box names the chord you have built. Tap it to summon the chord generator \u2014 pick a root, quality, and inversion and the instruments retune themselves to it. Preview it before you commit.',targetId:'studio-chordbox'},{tab:'studio',title:'Equal Temperament vs. Just Intonation',text:'Equal Temperament (ET) splits the octave into twelve identical steps \u2014 convenient, but every chord is a little impure. Just Intonation (JI) instead tunes each note to a pure whole-number ratio of the root, the way a fine string quartet leans into a chord. Tap "JI" and listen for the beating between notes vanish.',targetId:'studio-ji'},{tab:'learn',title:'The Learning Path',text:'A curriculum from intervals to inversions. This glowing node is your current lesson \u2014 tap it to begin. Lessons unlock in order, and the \u2605 test nodes guard each unit; pass one to open the next.',targetId:'learn-current'},{tab:'learn',title:'How progress is tracked',text:'Every answer is graded and fed to your six skill ratings \u2014 you need not keep score yourself. A lesson completes at 70%, a unit test at 90%. Miss a unit and you may replay its test as often as your patience allows.'},{tab:'learn',title:'Free Practice',text:'The \u221e button opens endless practice: choose exactly what to drill \u2014 question style, how many answers, which instrument, ET or JI \u2014 and go. No locks, no mercy, no unit tests barring the way.',targetId:'learn-free'},{tab:'scores',title:'Score Analysis \xb7 a photo',text:'Bring a photograph of the passage you are rehearsing as a reference \u2014 tap here to attach one. You may flip between the photo and clean notation of the chords you enter.',targetId:'scores-photo'},{tab:'scores',title:'Adding & adjusting chords',text:'"+ Add Chord" annotates the passage chord by chord. Each chord can be voiced, given per-note instruments, doubled, drag-reordered, and tuned in cents \u2014 then played back as a progression at any speed.',targetId:'scores-addchord'},{tab:'scores',title:'The tuning exercise',text:'Once you have entered chords, "Create Custom Exercise" plays your progression and then hides a false intonation in each chord. Open one chord at a time and drag each note until it rings true \u2014 I could always hear the wolf in the pack.'},{tab:'tools',title:'The Metronome \xb7 accents',text:'A metronome with character: choose its sound, meter, and subdivisions \u2014 even stack up to three layers. Tap the beat dots to move the emphasis; the first beat leads, the others follow.',targetId:'tools-beatdots'},{tab:'tools',title:'Ghost Mode',text:'Ghost Mode silences beats on purpose \u2014 at random, or in blocks of whole measures \u2014 so you must keep the pulse in your own head and land exactly where the click returns. A cruel teacher. An effective one.',targetId:'tools-ghost'},{tab:'tools',title:'Accelerando / Ritardando',text:'Set a start and end tempo and the metronome ramps between them over a chosen number of bars \u2014 accelerando to press forward, ritardando to broaden. Drag the curve to seek within it.',targetId:'tools-accel'},{tab:'tools',title:'The Tuner',text:'Switch to the Tuner here. Play or sing and the needle tells you the truth; sustain a drone to tune against \u2014 use headphones, lest the microphone hear the drone and flatter you. On the web you may even record a few bars and hear yourself back over the click.',targetId:'tools-tunertab'},{tab:'profile',title:'Your Profile \xb7 tracking progress',text:'Every answer feeds six skill ratings, each climbing an Elo curve as you beat harder questions. A chart plots your rise; time spent on each room is counted; nothing you practise is wasted.'},{tab:'profile',title:'What you can unlock',text:'Ratings pass through tiers \u2014 Dirt, Stone, Bronze, Silver, Gold, Diamond, Gem, Genius \u2014 and twenty-five leveled medals reward streaks, accuracy, corrections, hours, and mastery. Reach the summit and you may keep company with composers.'},{tab:null,title:'Replay anytime',text:"That is the tour. Should you wish to endure me again, open this \u2261 menu and choose 'Tutorial'. Each room also explains itself as you use it.",targetId:'menu'},{tab:null,title:'Farewell',text:'Enough talk. Music is a higher revelation than all wisdom and philosophy \u2014 go and train the organ that receives it. Muss es sein? Es muss sein. Begin.'}]},286,[],"lib/tutorialScript.ts");
